Magnolia Bakery's Cupcakes

1 c (2 sticks) unsalted butter + extra for greasing
1 1/4 c ap flour + extra for dusting
1 1/2 c self-rising flour
1 c milk
1 tsp vanilla
2 c sugar
4 large eggs at room temp

Preheat oven to 350F. Grease and lightly flour 2x12 cup muffin tins and then line with cupcake papers. Mix the flours together in a bowl. In a glass measure, mix the milk and vanilla. In a large bowl, cream the butter with an electric mixer at medium speed until smooth. Add the sugar gradually and beat until fluffy (~3min). Add the eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually add the flour, alternating with the milk, beating well after each addition. Spoon the batter into muffin cups about 3/4 full. Bake until the tops of the cupcakes spring back when lightly touched, 20-22 min. Remove from the pans and cook on a rack before icing.


Buttercream Vanilla Icing

1 c (2 sticks) unsalted butter, softened
8 c confectioners' sugar
1/2 c milk
2 tsp vanilla
optional - food coloring

Place the butter in a large mixing bowl. Add 4 c of sugar and then the milk and vanilla. Beat until smooth and creamy. Gradually add the remaining sugar, 1 c at a time, until the icing is thick enough to spread. 

Notes:
Can add cream cheese instad of some of the cream (milk). Can also add other flavorings besides vanilla.
